name: float_f64_smallest_positive_subnormal
description: |
  This is the smallest positive non-zero binary64 value, 2^-1074. Hardware,
  compiler modes, foreign-function boundaries, or accelerated kernels using
  flush-to-zero may turn it into positive zero, changing equality, loop
  termination, underflow behavior, and division results.
format: hex
decode-as: f64-le
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "subnormal"
  - "underflow"
---
01 00 00 00 00 00 00 00   # 0x0000000000000001: 2^-1074
